            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "SGTM. The cmdline is primarily for interactive use, so doing whatever feels most natural/DWIM is usually best.\n\n> Due to the prevalence of third-party `:FooLog` commands opening a log file in a new tab instead of in the same window, `:editlog` no longer wraps `:edit`, but instead `:tabnew`.\n\nI am always skeptical when this is raised. Third party plugins, even very popular ones, do a lot of cringe stuff.  Also not sure it was  good idea for checkhealth to open a new tab.\n\nUsers can opt-in to split/tab via `:hor` and `:tab`, whereas the opposite is not true. By default we should just open a buffer.",
