        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Changing the log level comes to mind as a frequent ad-hoc/interactive operation.\n\nThat's a good point. IMO `:log` should still be for viewing logs, but before the PR is merged we should make a decision on if it should be named `:log`. I can always change the name to something else once everything else is complete.\n\n> Just so these alternative names have been coined: `:logedit`, `:logopen`, `:openlog`, `:viewlog`, `:logview`. Feel free to ignore. \n\nIf we end up not naming the command `:log`, my favorite of this list is `:logopen`. The name definitely needs to start with `:log*`, so that `:log<Tab>` completes all commands that interact with logs.",
            "created_at": "2026-03-30T19:57:41Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/35082#issuecomment-4157789571",
            "id": 4157789571,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/35082",
